snippet.textDisplay:
That grey pow is called stone dust, you can get it in bags at any home improvement store or in bulk at any garden center or any yard where you can buy sand or dirt, like the one where you got your Granular A (gravel) for the forest road. It's actually the same powder that was mixed in with the gravel and is what gives it that concrete-like quality when you tamp it. If you're building a stone patio, it's what you put right under your stone, that stuff is like magic


I would definitely get a yard or two so you can use it, just make sure to throw a tarp over it because the rain will wash the fine stuff away pretty fast when it's loose. Also put a tarp in your truck bed because it's pretty messy but won't damage the tarp
